{
  // CI build-gate tsconfig (bl-200). Extends the base tsconfig but DROPS
  // `scripts` from the exclude list, so a standalone `tsc --noEmit` typechecks
  // the WHOLE repo INCLUDING `scripts/*.ts`. The base `tsconfig.json` excludes
  // `scripts`, and `next build` only typechecks files inside the Next.js
  // compilation graph — so standalone CLI scripts (e.g.
  // scripts/eval-classification.ts) are never gated by CI without this. A type
  // error here is an unambiguous "build is broken" signal (the `build-gate`
  // job in .github/workflows/ci.yml).
  //
  // ROOT CAUSE this closes (bl-200 / S283 retro): a `tsc` break in a
  // standalone CLI script (the since-retired ledger-cli, ID-165) sat
  // undetected on main ~4 sessions because no CI job typechecked scripts/.
  //
  // `supabase`, `mcp-apps`, `docs-site` stay excluded: generated DB types,
  // self-contained Vite single-file builds, and the docs site each carry their
  // own toolchains/tsconfigs and are not part of this repo's typecheck surface.
  //
  // SCRIPTS COVERAGE (bl-213, S285): the full `scripts/**` surface is now
  // gated — the 18 accepted-debt exclusions that bl-200 carried (41
  // pre-existing tsc errors) have all been fixed and removed. The fixes were
  // type-only: typed Supabase clients (`createClient<Database>` +
  // `SupabaseClient<Database>` helper params, replacing untyped `never`
  // clients), a minimal Bun ambient (`scripts/bun-ambient.d.ts`) for the
  // `Bun` / `import.meta.dir` globals (full `@types/bun` was rejected — its
  // DOM-global overrides break ~120 app/test files; see tsconfig.json
  // `types`), a generic `emitResponse` in `tools/ast-dataflow/cli.ts`, and
  // Json casts at JSONB-column boundaries. Every `scripts/*.ts` is now gated
  // BY DEFAULT — nothing escapes.
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    // The base tsconfig sets `incremental: true`, which writes a
    // `tsconfig.ci.tsbuildinfo` cache file. CI runners are ephemeral (no
    // cache benefit) and the artefact would otherwise litter the working tree
    // / need a gitignore entry. Disable it for this gate.
    "incremental": false
  },
  "exclude": [
    "node_modules",
    "supabase",
    "mcp-apps",
    "docs-site",
    "tools/ast-dataflow/__tests__/fixtures",
    "vitest.integration.config.ts"
  ]
}
